fields.object_repr: Classic Landscape Design and Environment Planning

fields.title: Spatial Analysis
fields.content:
Combining data and skills, from coding to software and hardware.
Generating analysis based on  logic and team communication.
Leading to a solution from group decision making. 


Though Planning can never be fully comprehensive, but with more data collection and analysis, can lead to better plans.

Building roadmaps to improve current environment, view from big scale and work on detail.

fields.title: Machine Learning
fields.content:
Application usage of Machine Learning

Prediction and Categorization:
Road pavement categorization, using transfer learning of tensorflow imagenet model to distinguish asphalt, pebble, tiles, and grass.

Automation of works:
Using trained model from ImageAI to impletment privacy protection.  Blurring out driving plate and people.
Futher applications on Traffic analysis of farmlands.
fields.summary:

fields.content:
Collection of different sources,
experience with Landsat, Sentinel using ArcGIS & ENVI

Referring to index interpretation, such as NDVI
(the title image is the NDVI of Taipei in 2018)

DEM retrive, Image calliberation, creating basemap data for further project usage.

fields.title: Web Application
fields.content:
Park service level evaluation of Taipei:

Base map: extract DEM, with sptatial analysis generating watershed and basin

Accessibility: using network analysis to find the walking distance to all residents in the city

Health: NDVI showing the quality of vegatation in surrounding parks and mountains

Air quality: distribution of pm 2.5 with the influence of air current

final result with showcases of a serie of maps
